The paper presents a new neural network architecture for embedding multi-relational graphs into a continuous vector space, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with structured data and link prediction, which are common topics in database research, suggesting cs.DB (Databases) as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and the use of large-scale data, which is relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
